<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal tergum 1 smooth, with strong luster; other terga densely and minutely microsculptured, with feeble luster; tergum 1 with broad and round incision, lateral carina low but distinct, anterior corner angulate, posterior corner not produced; subgenital plate strongly protruded in middle 1/3. Lancet with 54 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14L</figureCitation>
), middle serrulae weakly narrowed toward truncate apex, with 2-3 proximal and distal subbasal teeth, distance between serrulae 1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14O</figureCitation>
); lance long and slender, subapical annuli broadened, total length of annuli 5.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 20 mm (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14B</figureCitation>
). Body color and structures similar to female except for head hardly dilated behind eye in dorsal view and antenna about 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head breadth; apex of subgenital plate roundish; gonoforceps as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14M</figureCitation>
, penis valve as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Asicimbex ulmusvorus (Yang, 1996) comb. nov. A female in dorsal view B male in dorsal view C head of female in dorsal view D head of female in front view E mesopleuron and metapleuron F antenna of female G head of male in dorsal view H head of male in front view I thoracic notum J hind tarsus K lateral side of abdomen L lancet M gonoforceps N penis valve O middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707237" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">14N</figureCitation>
.
